# Pipeline configuration — copy to .pipeline.env and edit before running anything.
#
# .pipeline.env is gitignored so each developer keeps their own local config.
# Run `make init` for an interactive setup that writes this file for you.

# GitHub repo the pipeline operates on (issues, PRs, branches).
# Format: owner/name
TARGET_REPO=owner/repo

# k3d cluster name. Arbitrary, but must be unique on your machine.
CLUSTER_NAME=mypipeline-poc

# In-cluster registry name. Arbitrary, but must match in scripts and operator.
REGISTRY_NAME=mypipeline-registry

# Devcontainer image name pushed into the registry by `make seed-image`.
# Final image reference becomes: ${REGISTRY_NAME}:5000/${DEVCONTAINER_IMAGE}:latest
DEVCONTAINER_IMAGE=mypipeline-devcontainer

# --- Credentials (consumed by `make secrets`; can also be exported in your shell) ---
# These are secrets — keep them out of version control. .pipeline.env is gitignored.

# Git identity for the agent's commits.
# GIT_AUTHOR_NAME=Your Name
# GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL=you@example.com

# Claude auth — set exactly ONE:
# CLAUDE_OAUTH_TOKEN=sk-ant-oat01-...   # subscription billing (local dev)
# CLAUDE_TOKEN=sk-ant-...               # API billing (shared/CI)

# GitHub auth — two options:
#
# 1. Long-lived PAT (simplest). Needs Contents/Issues/PullRequests read+write on
#    the target repo. Also used by the triage CronJob.
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_...
#
# 2. GitHub App (recommended for public repos). The operator mints ~1h
#    installation tokens per task instead of mounting a long-lived secret into
#    agent pods. See docs/github-app-setup.md. GITHUB_TOKEN is still used by the
#    triage CronJob and as a fallback, so set it too.
# GH_APP_ID=123456
# GH_INSTALLATION_ID=12345678
# GH_APP_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH=~/.config/agentic-dev-pipeline/github-app.pem
